Weidmann Seeks Partners to Oppose ECB Bond Purchases, FAZ Says

-- B y   J e f f   B l a c k
-- 
2011-09-21T09:17:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/weidmann-seeks-partners-to-oppose-ecb-bond-purchases-faz-says.html
Bundesbank President Jens Weidmann
invited fellow European Central Bank council members to a
meeting to shore up opposition to the ECB’s bond purchases, the
 Frankfurter Allgemeine Zeitung  reported without saying where it
got the information.  The newspaper said while the exact timing of the meeting
remains unclear,  Yves Mersch , governor of Luxembourg’s central
bank, and Klaas Knot, president of the Dutch central bank, were
among those invited.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Black in Frankfurt 
 jblack25@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Craig Stirling at   cstirling1@bloomberg.net  